description.narrative: By 2025, parents, caregivers, children and pregnant women benefit from strengthened, evidence-informed communication approaches to improve their health care practices., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Early Childhood Development, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, more neonates, infants and children survive and thrive, and fewer women die during pregnancy and childbirth.
